column2: iMotions synchronization timestamp. Relative to data recording start
column3: Can be used to filter data from: SlideEvents
column9: Can be used to filter data from: Eyetracker Gazepoint GP3 (Standalone)
column10: X-coordinate of the gaze point (2D) of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)
column11: Y-coordinate of the gaze point (2D) of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)
column12: X-coordinate of the gaze point (2D) of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)
column13: Y-coordinate of the gaze point (2D) of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)
column14: Pupil diameter of the left eye
column15: Pupil diameter of the right eye
column17: Estimated distance between the eye-tracker and the left eye
column18: Estimated distance between the eye-tracker and the right eye
column19: X-coordinate of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)
column20: Y-coordinate of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)
column21: X-coordinate of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)
column22: Y-coordinate of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)
column23: Can be used to filter data from: R Analysis GazeAnalysis I-VT filter
column24: Gaze data X-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen). Average of the X-coordinates of the left and right eye.
column25: Gaze data Y-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen). Average of the Y-coordinates of the left and right eye.
column26: Gaze data X-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen) with missing coordinates interpolated. Average of the X-coordinates of the left and right eye.
column27: Gaze data Y-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen) with missing coordinates interpolated. Average of the Y-coordinates of the left and right eye.
column28: Estimated distance between the eye-tracker and the eyes, with missing values interpolated. Average of the eye tracker's distance to the left and right eye.
column29: Angular velocity of the gaze at the current sample point, i.e. how fast the eyes are moving at this point in time.
column30: Angular acceleration of the gaze at the current sample point, i.e. how much the eyes increased in speed at the current sample.
column31: Fixation number, counting from start of the recording.
column32: Fixation number, counting from start of the stimulus.
column33: X-coordinate of the fixation centroid (relative to top-left corner of the screen).
column34: Y-coordinate of the fixation centroid (relative to top-left corner of the screen).
column35: Start time of the fixation (relative to recording start).
column36: End time of the fixation (relative to recording start).
column38: Dispersion of the fixation, i.e. how much the fixation's gaze points are spread out.
column39: Saccade number, counting from start of the recording.
column40: Saccade number, counting from start of the stimulus.
column41: Start time of the saccade (relative to recording start).
column42: End time of the saccade (relative to recording start).
column44: Amplitude of the saccade, i.e. angular distance that the eyes travelled from start point to end point.
column45: Peak velocity of the saccade, i.e. the maximal speed of the eyes during this saccade.
column46: Peak acceleration of the saccade, i.e.  the maximal increase in speed of the eyes during this saccade.
column47: Peak deceleration of the saccade, i.e. the maximal decrease in speed of the eyes during this saccade.
column48: Direction of the saccade from its start point to end point, indicated as clockwise angles: 0 degrees mean a horizontal saccade from left to right, 90 degrees a vertical saccade from top to bottom.
